{"TopicId":166786,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.12.x] Through The Eyes of a Kerbal","CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-23T10:53:01Z","PageNum":5,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Stone Blue","CreatedById":77721,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-07T14:37:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223767408\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221586268417\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n29 minutes ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat is \u0022TURD\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022117203\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9179262749\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/174188-18x-textures-unlimited-recolour-depot/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:209px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"acr_8133","CreatedById":195401,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-08T11:16:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223767408\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221586268417\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat is \u0022TURD\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTextures Unlimited Recolor Depot.. that mod\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nEdit: although that seems not to be the issue, instead I believe that it is TextureReplacer that\u0027s causing the problem\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-04-08T11:18:44Z\u0022 title=\u002204/08/2020 11:18  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EApril 8, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by acr_8133\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"horace","CreatedById":166359,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-22T00:17:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis it ok to use it on the exteral command seat?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-06T15:53:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223774183\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587514658\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166359\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022horace\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/21/2020 at 8:17 PM, horace said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis it ok to use it on the exteral command seat?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, won\u0027t work.\u00A0 Sorry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TH3P41NTR41N","CreatedById":126209,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-15T22:59:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223232328\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221512120328\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Enceos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/1/2017 at 1:25 AM, Enceos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLove this mod a lot! It inspired me to make a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E Holo Visor prop with EVA Propellant level indicator. Available in my \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E Wearable Props.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/x17Qn0yQwqI?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhat version of that props mod and ksp are you using? iim using v1.9.1 n everything seems to work except the helmets and guns n was really tryna get the glass helmet with first person. during EVA i can place the helmet on the ground or even mount it on something with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E but nothing happens when i go to actually equip it \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EasyAce","CreatedById":62958,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-18T19:49:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have this wierd issue that I think might be two issues...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile IVA in Mk1 I happened to click somewhere in the cockpit and the perspective of the Kerbal moved closer to the \u0022roof\u0022. It is like he is standing up to see out of the window... which is cool, but also moves the view away from the RPM screens. I am not able to \u0022move back\u0022 into the seat. Any smart commands?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso I am not able to switch back to external view again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes I did do some changes and tweaks to force myself to IVA but I kind of regret it and am not able to turn it back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTried deleting the mod with no luck. So I installed it again guessing that I would then get the option in the settings page to tur nof the force IVA setting... but still not able to get to the 3rd persion view.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny suggestions?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-18T20:37:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223787302\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221589831359\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002262958\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022EasyAce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n47 minutes ago, EasyAce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have this wierd issue that I think might be two issues...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile IVA in Mk1 I happened to click somewhere in the cockpit and the perspective of the Kerbal moved closer to the \u0022roof\u0022. It is like he is standing up to see out of the window... which is cool, but also moves the view away from the RPM screens. I am not able to \u0022move back\u0022 into the seat. Any smart commands?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso I am not able to switch back to external view again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes I did do some changes and tweaks to force myself to IVA but I kind of regret it and am not able to turn it back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTried deleting the mod with no luck. So I installed it again guessing that I would then get the option in the settings page to tur nof the force IVA setting... but still not able to get to the 3rd persion view.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny suggestions?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis has nothing to do with this mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EasyAce","CreatedById":62958,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-18T20:57:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223787342\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221589834249\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis has nothing to do with this mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk sorry then. My guess was that this mod changed some keybindings or made restrictions to some keybindings working - hence this mod might effect my games possibilities to visit 3rd person view. But if you say so I will trust that. Will look elsewhere then.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"slysh","CreatedById":204811,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-22T19:02:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it possible to rotate kerbal with mouse\u00A0or to control him as it was without this mod?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LtMtz","CreatedById":166455,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-26T13:40:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E I have a problem with flickering when in first person EVA. I recorded a video of it: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://streamable.com/chefi2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EVideo\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe flickering only disappears when running the renderer in lowest or low setting. I asked in scatterer thread already beacause i thought it\u0027s related to the common 1.9 shadow problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was told it could be an issue with nearClipPlane being overridden. I\u0027m running the game on dx11. Is it only me who has this problem and can it be solved?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks in advance!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Neil Kermstrong","CreatedById":201201,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-21T21:03:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis mod is cool and works for 1.10.1 but I have two things to say/ask:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. The first person feels too much dizzy, and it\u0027s probably because of the fov, so is there anyway to change the FOV? The ALT \u002B Scroll doesn\u0027t work\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. Is there any way to revert the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E controls to the normal ones? I dont like the ones used on vessels\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beetlecat","CreatedById":92207,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-21T21:28:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223789485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221590174162\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022slysh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/22/2020 at 12:02 PM, slysh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it possible to rotate kerbal with mouse\u00A0or to control him as it was without this mod?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if mouse aim flight would work?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002250204\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4260591592\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/137830-19x-mouse-aim-flight-113-pilot-airplanes-with-your-mouse/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Neil Kermstrong","CreatedById":201201,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-21T21:39:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223841897\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221598045329\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002292207\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Beetlecat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, Beetlecat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if mouse aim flight would work?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002250204\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3469141502\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/137830-19x-mouse-aim-flight-113-pilot-airplanes-with-your-mouse/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:213px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am not him but that mod looks good, I\u0027ll install and test it and if it works I\u0027ll tell you and him\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Neil Kermstrong","CreatedById":201201,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-21T22:16:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223841897\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221598045329\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002292207\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Beetlecat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n47 minutes ago, Beetlecat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if mouse aim flight would work?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002250204\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2289958906\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/137830-19x-mouse-aim-flight-113-pilot-airplanes-with-your-mouse/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:213px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223789485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221590174162\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022slysh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/22/2020 at 4:02 PM, slysh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it possible to rotate kerbal with mouse\u00A0or to control him as it was without this mod?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSadly it doesn\u0027t work\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gordon Dry","CreatedById":163177,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-01T23:31:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223791262\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221590500423\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166455\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LtMtz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/26/2020 at 3:40 PM, LtMtz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a problem with flickering when in first person EVA\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSame here. I got only scatterer (no \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Environmental Visual Enhancement (mod)\u0022\u003EEVE\u003C/abbr\u003E etc.) to fix the shadows issue and get a little better visual.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut in first person EVA there still is flickering as soon as the orientation of view is slightly changed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"BrunoViking","CreatedById":207963,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-02T19:26:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI really loved the idea of 1st person\u00A0EVA\u003Cbr\u003E\nWill it work with 1.10.1?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-12-02T19:28:43Z\u0022 title=\u002212/02/2020 07:28  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 2, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by BrunoViking\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beetlecat","CreatedById":92207,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-03T01:11:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223888873\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221606937203\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022207963\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022BrunoViking\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, BrunoViking said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI really loved the idea of 1st person\u00A0EVA\u003Cbr\u003E\nWill it work with 1.10.1?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeems to! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/kerbal-forum-uploads/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bvsveera","CreatedById":184860,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-04T17:20:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeems to be working as well in 1.11.1 as it did in 1.10\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoogyRev","CreatedById":209725,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-14T21:45:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is a great mod. I don\u0027t understand why a first person view isn\u0027t included in the game. I can\u0027t seem to get the jet pack thrusters to work at all. Is it possible to use the normal Kerbal control axes from the settings page while in FP? Also, is it possible to use the normal camera axes (with POV hat) to look around the inside of the helmet? I can only use the mouse to look\u00A0around.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-03-14T21:45:51Z\u0022 title=\u002203/14/2021 09:45  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 14, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by DoogyRev\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Zensei","CreatedById":210671,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-19T06:29:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223791262\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221590500423\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166455\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LtMtz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/26/2020 at 9:40 AM, LtMtz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E I have a problem with flickering when in first person EVA. I recorded a video of it: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://streamable.com/chefi2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EVideo\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe flickering only disappears when running the renderer in lowest or low setting. I asked in scatterer thread already beacause i thought it\u0027s related to the common 1.9 shadow problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was told it could be an issue with nearClipPlane being overridden. I\u0027m running the game on dx11. Is it only me who has this problem and can it be solved?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks in advance!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid you end up finding a solution to the flickering? I\u0027m getting the same issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SiCaRiO31","CreatedById":158163,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-09T19:25:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223942282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221616135391\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210671\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Zensei\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/19/2021 at 7:29 AM, Zensei said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid you end up finding a solution to the flickering? I\u0027m getting the same issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsame here. flickering terrain, using scatterer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Zensei","CreatedById":210671,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-10T04:33:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223951788\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221617996346\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022158163\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SiCaRiO31\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, SiCaRiO31 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsame here. flickering terrain, using scatterer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSort of:\u00A0I uninstalled the mod and am currently using \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/145633-1111-hullcam-vds-continued/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EHullcam VDS\u003C/a\u003E to do first-person EVAs (right click on kerbal and select \u0027Activate Camera\u0027 to activate first-person view, then use Backspace to cancel first-person view). No matter what I tried, I couldn\u0027t solve the flickering issue. I\u0027ve had no problems with Hullcam thus far.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SiCaRiO31","CreatedById":158163,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-14T22:26:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, I followed the instructions at the first post but cant find the way to change the keybindings. Im on 1.11.2.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002220210515000500-1.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/xYdd6yL/20210515000500-1.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-15T12:11:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223972649\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221621031191\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022158163\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SiCaRiO31\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, SiCaRiO31 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfollowed the instructions at the first post but cant find the way to change the keybindings. Im on 1.11.2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid you try editing the file specified:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nThe\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003EThroughTheEyes/PluginData/options.cfg contains the following, you can change them with a text editor:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cli style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\ntoggleFirstPersonKey\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nEVAKey\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nrecoverKey\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nreviewDataKey\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SiCaRiO31","CreatedById":158163,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-15T12:44:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223972928\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221621080672\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid you try editing the file specified:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nThe\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003EThroughTheEyes/PluginData/options.cfg contains the following, you can change them with a text editor:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cli style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\ntoggleFirstPersonKey\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nEVAKey\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nrecoverKey\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nreviewDataKey\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI found that field, however I was under the impression that you could change the keys for translating the kerbal too. For instance, I want to swap I and K to translate up and down respectively, instead of down and up, but found no line to edit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}